        Recycling is the process of collecting and processing materials that would otherwise be thrown away to create new products. This helps to conserve natural resources, reduce landfill waste, and decrease pollution. For example, old newspapers can be recycled into new paper products, plastic bottles can be turned into new plastic containers, and glass jars can be melted down to make new glass bottles. By recycling, we can help to reduce waste, protect the environment, and preserve natural resources for future generations.
